## PFLICHT: Neue Service-Funktionen — Checkliste (Risiko A + B)

Jede neue `export async function` die `.from('org-scoped-table')` aufruft MUSS:

```typescript
// ✅ RICHTIG: expliziter orgId Parameter + assertOrgContext Guard
export async function getNewFeatureData(
  agencyId: string,               // ← Pflicht-Parameter, kein Optional
  opts?: { limit?: number }
): Promise<MyType[]> {
  if (!assertOrgContext(agencyId, 'getNewFeatureData')) return [];
  try {
    const { data, error } = await supabase
      .from('new_feature_table')
      .select('*')
      .eq('agency_id', agencyId)  // ← Defense-in-Depth: expliziter Filter + RLS
      .limit(opts?.limit ?? 100);
    if (error) { console.error('getNewFeatureData error:', error); return []; }
    return (data ?? []) as MyType[];
  } catch (e) {
    console.error('getNewFeatureData exception:', e);
    return [];
  }
}
```

**Verbotene Muster:**
```typescript
// ❌ VERBOTEN: kein org-Filter, reine RLS-Abhängigkeit
export async function getNewFeatureData(): Promise<MyType[]> {
  const { data } = await supabase.from('new_feature_table').select('*');
  return data ?? [];
}

// ❌ VERBOTEN: leerer String in Audit-Log
void logBookingAction(orgId ?? '', 'booking_created', id, {...});

// ❌ VERBOTEN: stille Return ohne Log
if (!orgId) return [];

// ✅ RICHTIG: Guard mit Log
if (!assertOrgContext(orgId, 'myFunction')) return [];
```

**Org-scoped Tabellen (immer Filter erforderlich):**
`model_applications`, `recruiting_chat_threads`, `option_requests`, `booking_events`,
`calendar_entries`, `activity_logs`, `organization_members`, `organization_subscriptions`

